caption: Sweet staff, fast takeout service, delicious food.
One of the best/most loved mexican spots on the island in my opinion.

If your expectations are "Authentic" Mexican, then stop reading & find another spot! First time here & definitely last time here.  -Chilaquiles: it was serve a la carte. (No beans or rice) Chilaquiles arrived swimming in sauce. The tortilla chips was store bought for sure. The only way i can describe the experience is: -Tortilla chips, swimming in sauce, with scrambled eggs on top and sprinkle of shredded chicken & cheese!  Let me tell you about the Carne en chile: First i asked, "Chile Rojo or Verde, which one is the spicey one?" The response from the only latino guy there was: "Non of them are spicey..."  FML!  I order the red one! It tasted really sweet. Not what i wanted at all..  *Furthermore, i order a michelada and usually they serve the glass with mix in it & the beer next to it. Another common one is: they pour the beer in the mich and set the left over beer next to the glass. What i got was a salty water down michelada. I don't even know if it had beer..😢

I had the Los Chaparros Super Burrito.  The flavors were great and the burrito was enormous.  I am returning to this establishment.  The wait staff was prompt and friendly.  The food was delivered promptly to our table.  I enjoyed the green sauce on my entree.  The food prices are fair and are not discounted by smaller cuts of meat within the burrito.  The restrooms were clean and showed pride in the care for their establishment.  I left full and happy.

Excellent Mexican food. The salsa that they provided had a very nice flavor. If you mix in the hot sauce it tastes better as it needed more spice in my opinion. My dad and I each ordered a burrito. Next time I will just get a appetizer and burrito to share as the portion sizes were very large. Will come again.

Been many places, such as Mexico, San Diego, Miami to mention a few and Los Chaparros was by far the best mexican restaurant for the food and friendly service we have ever been to. The shredded beef and carne asada steak was Outstanding! Would highly recommend this restrauant to anyone who loves mexican 🥝!

Been to this place before and always had great food and the service was always excellent. I don't know if they changed cooks or the owner isn't around during Covid to keep the standards up. Only 1 in 4 didn't have a problem with the food, but it wasn't the best Mexican food around like it used to be.

Hands down the best Mexican restaurant with excellent service. We had a reservation and was waiting for a while because they were full. We didn’t mind waiting but they took all their effort to reassure us that we will be seated soon. They didn’t have to do it but they went out their way to make us feel welcomed. I will definitely come back, not just because of the service but their great food too. Highly recommend!

They only get two stars for their super friendly staff that are very nice and accommodating, but their food is joke (would have only been one star based on the food). I ordered carnitas.  It was dried out little chunks of carnitas with no juicyness or flavor. The beans taste like canned refried beans and the garnishes are minimal. Tortillas aren't fresh. The rice was equally as pathetic. I would get better food from a whole in the wall and pay less.  My family ordered the chile relleno that was small and sad and just all around sad.  Again, super friendly staff and (very small) bag of chips and salsa are their only saving grace. Can't really call this Mexican food at all.

I recently moved to Hawaii and have been on the hunt for great Mexican and kept finding myself disappointed. First off, I am Mexican and I know authentic Mexican food. From my mother and grandmother who were born & raised in Mexico, nothing gets as close to authentic as Los Chaparros. My husband and I have been searching for great Mexican food since we moved here but we soon discovered great Mexican food here is a rarity. We noticed all of the amazing 5-star reviews stating the same so we had to give this place a shot. We we were not disappointed and we will become frequent customers moving forward. For all of the 4-star reviews who loved the food but had a complaint having nothing to do with the quality is ridiculous. Grow up!! I want to know about the food!!! I don’t care if parking was tough, the salsa wasn’t spicy enough for you (everyone has a different preference, they are appealing to the masses), or if you were having a bad hair day. #realtalk #luckywelivehawaii 🤙🏼

I wasn't a fan of the salsa they served with tortilla chips when we sat down... but, hey, it was free, so no harm there! If you like Mexican food, please treat yourself to this place!

This place hurt my heart. Plasticky cheese, a bloated menu where everything is done but nothing really done well, a dusty and unkempt front of house (thick coating on railings, piñatas, everywhere...), and an overabundance of sauce everywhere to cover a multitude of sins against Mexican food of all regions. The sad chile relleno was flat, old, and covered in cheese that stuck to the plate. Tortillas tasted and looked purchased.  The only standout has been the well-seasoned, tender meat in the carnitas (forget the wasteland of beans and rice).  What started as a mom and pop shop making home-cooked food has unfortunately degenerated into a tired spot in need of inspiration, a deep cleaning, and a severe menu pare-down.  Sweet but slow and occasionally forgetful customer service.  Terrible parking lot with little on street parking on Beretania as an alternative.

It was way more expensive than I like for these things (1 drink, 1 extra chips and my ala carte beans and single enchilada for about $15.00 not including tip), but like I said, I got my mexican food fix. I love Mexican food and, for the most part, thought my food was great. The tortilla chips they make were delicious, however, the salsa that came with them was disappointing. Their homemade was watery and not spicy at all. Since they make the salsa fresh themselves, it is possible that this was a single, poorly-made batch. The burrito and fish taco tasted excellent, though the salsa served was the same one that I didn't like coupled with a salsa verde that also wasn't particularly spicy.  I would have given 5 stars if the food was a tiny bit better. It is hard to please everybody, but the mammoth burrito could have used a really spicy salsa to go with it and I do not think this would be too difficult for the kitchen to offer, especially at a place like this. For example, I like the combination plate with a steak burrito (the meat is marinated in a blend of yummy spices) and a perfect crispy taco. I'm from Southern California, so I'm used to having a wide selection of Mexican food places to eat from - from the more upscale restaurants to little hole-in-the-wall places where you can see Mom and Pop cooking in the background. When my nephew wanted chicken tacos for dinner, we were a bit hesitant to get Mexican food in Hawaii. I am so glad that we found this place on Yelp; the food was delicious! I ordered the Super Chaparros Burrito which had pretty much everything in it and shredded beef (but you can choose from a variety of meats like ground beef, shredded chicken, shrimp, fish, etc.). I opted to get my burrito wet with green sauce and it was so good! The green sauce was pretty spicy (or at least I believe most people would find it spicy - I really like spicy food) but it wasn't super sour like a lot of other green sauces I've had before.  I got a michelada because it was one of their drink specials for Wednesday. You have your choice of beer selection for the michelada, and I opted to do my favorite, Dos Equis. It seemed like the michelada mix was kind of store bought, but it was palatable and still equally delicious. They had other specials that day as well like a lilikoi, passion fruit, margarita. I didn't have the chance to try this one but I will be sure to try it on my next visit.  The location of the place is a little on the sketchy side, but it's well worth the visit. It is quite a small location and they don't seem to have the largest staff so it can be a small wait for your food to come out, but the staff here are extremely friendly and courteous and the quality and taste of the food is definitely worth the wait.  One thing to note is that parking here is extremely limited, - there are about six parking spaces and there is only one entrance so you might find yourself in a tight parking situation. It's about a 50 minute walk from Waikiki, if you're staying at one of the numerous resorts here, so you might want to Lyft or Uber or be prepared to drive there yourself.
